<span class="displaytext">arlington, va -- today, u.s. representative lincoln diaz-balart (r-fl) issued the following statement on hispanic outreach efforts:<p>"unlike (candidate full), (candidate full) doesn't need an introduction to the hispanic community. (candidate full) has been working for more than two decades for the values, principles and issues latinos cares about. hispanics will elect the next president of the united states based on who has the best record, experience and is better prepared to move this country forward. (candidate full) wants to keep taxes low for hardworking families, and small business owners, (candidate full) has stated he will raise taxes. (candidate full) has an energy plan, and wants to lower gas prices, (candidate full) has no plan. (candidate full) always put this country first, (candidate full) changes his mind depending on the political calendar."</p></span>



